The '''white-bibbed swallow''' ('''''Hirundo nigrita'''''), also known as the '''white-throated blue swallow''', is a species of [[bird]] in the family [[Hirundinidae]].  It is widespread across the [[Tropical rainforest|African tropical rainforest]] ([[Dahomey Gap]] also).

